 but at device open time, but that's not always necessarily<br />possible. More importantly, it's not actually how things are done.<br /><br />So udev had better be fixed. The whole "no regressions" should be the<br />rule not just for the kernel, but it damn well should be the rule at<br />*least* also for projects like udev that are so closely related to the<br />kernel.<br /><br />The "I wish things were otherwise than they are" mindset is wishful<br />thinking. Reality is that probing - and firmware loading - happens<br />from the module init routines quite often, and it clearly used to<br />work. So udev broke. Fix it, don't argue that you wish things were<br />otherwise.<br /><br />            Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
